        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 8:28PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 827 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ottawa Lake, or near Blissfield, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Temperance and Lambertville around 845 PM EDT.
Luna Pier around 910 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Samaria, Riga, Toledo
Beach, Erie, Woodland Beach, Stony Point, La Salle, Bolles Harbor,
and Detroit Beach.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
